			<div class="padded">
				<h4>grid</h4>
				<p>The Artificial Framework makes use of a twelve-column grid with breaking points for mobile and tablet. On mobile, the grid is a single fluid column; on tablet a 720px grid of 60px columns; and on desktop a 960px grid of 80px columns.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="col-3">
			<div class="padded">
				<h4>colors</h4>
				<p>The entire Artificial color palette is contained in artificial-colors.scss. Each base hue also has a pale, dark, and darkest value. There are nine specified gradations of both warm and cool grey.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="col-3">
			<div class="padded">
				<h4>base</h4>
				<p>Base specifies the basics of an Artificial site's header, optional sub-header, and footer. Styles for artificial-base are contained in site-base, and should be edited to fit your site. </p>
			</div>
